  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Some `kubectl` commands fail when `--local` is used with no connection to an api server.\r\nAs far as I am aware, this is happening because of two main reasons:\r\n1. The command deals with thirdpartyresources, and therefore needs to handle unstructured objects and map them by hitting the api server later on (there is an issue explaining this further [here](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/46722)).\r\n2. The command uses `api.Registry.RESTMapper()` and is able to map a resource without hitting the server, but fails when printing the resource due to [PrinterForCommand defaulting to using the discovery client to map the given resource](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubectl/cmd/util/factory_builder.go#L52).\r\n\r\nA [PR has been opened (#45918)](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/45918) to address the second point above.\r\n\r\nBelow is a list of kubectl commands that are not addressed by #45918. They are commands that  support both thirdpartyresources and a `--local` flag:\r\n- [annotate](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubectl/cmd/annotate.go)\r\n- [label](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubectl/cmd/label.go)\r\n- [patch](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/kubectl/cmd/patch.go)\r\n\r\n**Kubernetes version** (use `kubectl version`):\r\n```\r\nClient Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"6+\", GitVersion:\"v1.6.0-alpha.2.5874+9a5aa313ec7cc9-dirty\", GitCommit:\"9a5aa313ec7cc99c0cb6e9e1ba388764e290d22d\", GitTreeState:\"dirty\", BuildDate:\"2017-06-06T20:04:03Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.8.1\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\ncc @fabianofranz @deads2k ",
